hopobject.body: Children with disabilities remedy pharmacy broadway glendale The rumors persist on who will be the head of the Fed. Japan’s Nikkei newspaper says Former Treasury Secretary Lawrence Summers will be named the next chairman of the Federal Reserve by President Obama. On Thursday more than 350 economists signed a letter to President Obama calling on him to nominate Federal Reserve Vice Chair Janet Yellen to be the next chairman.
